      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 255: start() can now be called multiple times without installing duplicate observers, but overlapping createTemporaryAccount() tasks are still allowed. A slower previous task can complete after a newer start(), overwrite tempAccount with a stale account id, drain pendingAuthResults for the wrong session, and route subsequent auth callbacks to the wrong temporary account. Track a generation token or cancel the previous task before starting a new one.\n```suggestion\nprivate var startGeneration \u003d 0\n\nfunc start() {\n    startGeneration +\u003d 1\n    let generation \u003d startGeneration\n    uiState \u003d .initial\n    tempAccount \u003d nil\n    pendingAuthResults.removeAll()\n    setupDeviceAuthObserver()\n    Task { @MainActor in\n        do {\n            let account \u003d try await accountsService.createTemporaryAccount()\n            guard generation \u003d\u003d startGeneration else { return }\n            tempAccount \u003d account\n            let bufferedResults \u003d pendingAuthResults\n            pendingAuthResults.removeAll()\n            for result in bufferedResults where result.accountId \u003d\u003d account {\n                updateDeviceAuthState(result: result)\n            }\n        } catch {\n            guard generation \u003d\u003d startGeneration else { return }\n            withAnimation { uiState \u003d .error(message: LinkDeviceError.networkError) }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```",
